1
00:00:36,266 --> 00:00:39,060
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

2
00:00:50,738 --> 00:00:53,074
A caged lion isn't intimidating.

3
00:00:54,492 --> 00:00:55,660
I can make fun of its whiskers

4
00:00:56,578 --> 00:00:58,538
or call it old or whatever.

5
00:00:59,914 --> 00:01:01,166
Until now,

6
00:01:02,584 --> 00:01:03,960
I've treated movies like a caged lion.

7
00:01:07,130 --> 00:01:07,964
But now,

8
00:01:08,798 --> 00:01:10,675
it's time to face the lion.

9
00:01:12,677 --> 00:01:14,596
I either have to run for my life…

10
00:01:19,309 --> 00:01:20,143
or…

11
00:01:23,188 --> 00:01:24,772
face it head-on.

12
00:02:12,028 --> 00:02:13,154
I'm good.

13
00:02:13,238 --> 00:02:14,489
Just take it.

14
00:02:21,871 --> 00:02:22,705
I read the revision.

15
00:02:24,916 --> 00:02:25,833
You did a good job.

16
00:02:27,710 --> 00:02:30,004
I was hoping to see you fail completely.

17
00:02:31,214 --> 00:02:32,590
Why the hell did you write so well?

18
00:02:33,508 --> 00:02:34,342
Now I'm tempted.

19
00:02:38,805 --> 00:02:39,639
It's good?

20
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,604
Hello.

21
00:02:48,189 --> 00:02:49,565
You're here early.

22
00:02:49,649 --> 00:02:52,485
We had to obtain
his award declination form first.

23
00:02:52,568 --> 00:02:53,444
Of course.

24
00:02:54,821 --> 00:02:55,655
Hello.

25
00:02:56,322 --> 00:02:57,323
Make sure you succeed.

26
00:02:58,992 --> 00:03:00,743
You betrayed me and left,

27
00:03:01,369 --> 00:03:02,453
so if you fail, you're done.

28
00:03:14,507 --> 00:03:16,759
We'll handle those separately.

29
00:03:16,843 --> 00:03:18,469
Clause 5 is important.

30
00:03:18,553 --> 00:03:20,680
"The right to create derivative works."

31
00:03:20,763 --> 00:03:24,225
Derivative works include
spin-offs or merchandise.

32
00:03:24,308 --> 00:03:26,811
Now, please enter your address
and everything else.

33
00:03:26,894 --> 00:03:28,312
WRITER'S NAME: HWANG DONG-MAN

34
00:03:28,396 --> 00:03:29,772
FILM PRODUCTION COMPANY:
KOPARK FILM PRODUCTION

35
00:03:31,899 --> 00:03:33,776
All right, let's take a photo.

36
00:03:33,860 --> 00:03:34,694
Director Hwang?

37
00:03:34,777 --> 00:03:36,946
Smile and say cheese.

38
00:03:37,030 --> 00:03:37,864
Cheese.

39
00:03:38,322 --> 00:03:39,240
Cheese.

40
00:03:40,783 --> 00:03:41,868
Congratulations.

41
00:03:41,951 --> 00:03:43,828
Contracts are freaking scary.

42
00:03:44,495 --> 00:03:45,830
If I don't finish this,

43
00:03:45,913 --> 00:03:48,958
I'll be liable
unless there's a natural disaster.

44
00:03:49,625 --> 00:03:51,627
That's just typical contract language.

45
00:03:52,712 --> 00:03:54,005
This is the beginning.

46
00:03:55,631 --> 00:03:57,425
I'll call you later.

47
00:03:57,508 --> 00:03:58,843
-I'm looking forward to it.
-Thank you.

48
00:04:01,471 --> 00:04:03,765
You'll probably get
a few plagiarism accusations.

49
00:04:03,848 --> 00:04:06,142
It's a story about AI and weather,

50
00:04:06,225 --> 00:04:08,686
and that alone guarantees
someone will claim it as theirs.

51
00:04:09,645 --> 00:04:10,897
Don't be scared.

52
00:04:11,481 --> 00:04:12,899
There are a lot of people

53
00:04:12,982 --> 00:04:16,027
who mistakenly think
they're the only ones with ideas.

54
00:04:16,611 --> 00:04:20,198
Just to be safe, were you involved in any
harassment issues that could resurface?

55
00:04:20,907 --> 00:04:22,450
-Come on.
-School bullying?

56
00:04:22,533 --> 00:04:24,077
I was the one who got beaten up.

57
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:26,371
If a scandal breaks out
after all that effort,

58
00:04:26,454 --> 00:04:28,414
it could be scrapped and not get released.

59
00:04:29,207 --> 00:04:32,126
Delete everything you posted online,
including social media.

60
00:04:32,210 --> 00:04:34,545
Don't think about what might be
problematic or not. Just delete it all.

61
00:04:35,171 --> 00:04:37,799
Not a single person in this world
wants you to succeed.

62
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:39,801
Except your parents.

63
00:04:41,636 --> 00:04:44,972
You used to cheer for others to fail
when their films got greenlit,

64
00:04:45,056 --> 00:04:47,350
so people like the old you
will come at you,

65
00:04:47,433 --> 00:04:48,935
hoping you fail.

66
00:04:51,062 --> 00:04:52,897
Let's revise one detail in the screenplay.

67
00:04:53,523 --> 00:04:57,777
If you want the evil protagonist
to suddenly turn good and make it work,

68
00:04:57,860 --> 00:04:59,612
he has to be truly evil at the start.

69
00:04:59,695 --> 00:05:02,532
Talking tough and yelling
doesn't make you scary.

70
00:05:03,991 --> 00:05:05,284
It feels like

71
00:05:05,868 --> 00:05:07,161
something is missing.

72
00:05:08,371 --> 00:05:09,580
A certain element of evil.

73
00:05:11,624 --> 00:05:13,793
Work on that so we can start casting.

74
00:05:14,585 --> 00:05:16,045
Who's your top choice?

75
00:05:17,338 --> 00:05:18,172
They're here.

76
00:05:19,340 --> 00:05:20,383
Hey.

77
00:05:20,466 --> 00:05:21,300
There you are.

78
00:05:22,552 --> 00:05:23,761
Come inside. It's cold.

79
00:05:25,930 --> 00:05:26,973
Hey.

80
00:05:27,890 --> 00:05:29,892
Hey, looking good.

81
00:05:31,978 --> 00:05:33,604
People like the old me.

82
00:05:39,152 --> 00:05:41,779
-Congratulations!
-Congrats, Hwang Dong-man!

83
00:05:42,572 --> 00:05:44,073
This year's winner!

84
00:05:45,283 --> 00:05:46,534
-Hwang Dong-man!
-Hwang Dong-man!

85
00:05:46,617 --> 00:05:49,120
-Hwang Dong-man!
-Hwang Dong-man!

86
00:05:49,203 --> 00:05:50,204
Jeez!

87
00:05:50,288 --> 00:05:51,706
Congratulations, my foot.

88
00:05:51,789 --> 00:05:53,541
I just picked up the winner's leftovers.

89
00:05:53,624 --> 00:05:54,709
Congrats, man!

90
00:05:54,792 --> 00:05:56,794
Hey, it's not easy to pick up leftovers.

91
00:05:56,878 --> 00:05:57,879
You can't beat luck!

92
00:05:57,962 --> 00:05:59,338
Not even talented people can--

93
00:06:03,593 --> 00:06:05,261
-Goodness gracious.
-Just come in.

94
00:06:08,806 --> 00:06:09,807
Hey, Dong-man.

95
00:06:09,891 --> 00:06:11,434
-Yeah?
-Eat up, okay?

96
00:06:12,059 --> 00:06:13,561
-Okay.
-Here, have this too.

97
00:06:14,187 --> 00:06:15,271
That's enough.

98
00:06:15,354 --> 00:06:18,149
It feels like I'm sending a son
to the military.

99
00:06:19,192 --> 00:06:20,234
Why am I getting so emotional?

100
00:06:21,235 --> 00:06:23,821
I wanted Dong-man to grow up carefree

101
00:06:23,905 --> 00:06:25,948
and never experience
anything ugly and harsh,

102
00:06:26,032 --> 00:06:28,534
but knowing you'll go through what I did

103
00:06:28,618 --> 00:06:29,785
makes me feel uneasy.

104
00:06:29,869 --> 00:06:31,704
You have to lead 200 people

105
00:06:31,787 --> 00:06:33,247
who won't listen for shit,

106
00:06:33,331 --> 00:06:35,458
and there are always
a few sour faces on set.

107
00:06:35,541 --> 00:06:37,418
Not a single scene goes as planned,

108
00:06:37,501 --> 00:06:40,087
and you stress over
whether you're blowing 20 billion won

109
00:06:40,171 --> 00:06:42,340
or ruining an actor's future.

110
00:06:43,299 --> 00:06:46,636
You'll consider running away hundreds,
maybe thousands of times.

111
00:06:47,511 --> 00:06:49,847
You're stressed
because you want to do well.

112
00:06:49,931 --> 00:06:52,892
I'm telling you,
I have zero desire to succeed.

113
00:06:52,975 --> 00:06:56,520
I'm going to fail completely
and talk about it for the rest of my life.

114
00:06:56,604 --> 00:06:58,356
Hey, you think it's easy to fail?

115
00:06:58,940 --> 00:07:00,733
You can only call it a hit or flop
if you finish it.

116
00:07:00,816 --> 00:07:02,276
Just leave him be.

117
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:05,821
Whether he hears military stories or not,
he won't know until he goes through it.

118
00:07:08,324 --> 00:07:10,284
-Here's some more food.
-Hey.

119
00:07:10,368 --> 00:07:12,078
Why are you bringing so much?

120
00:07:12,161 --> 00:07:12,995
You don't have to.

121
00:07:13,079 --> 00:07:14,413
Because it's a good day.

122
00:07:15,081 --> 00:07:17,250
Think of it as your last meal.

123
00:07:17,333 --> 00:07:19,001
From now on,

124
00:07:19,669 --> 00:07:21,254
anything you eat won't taste good.

125
00:07:22,755 --> 00:07:25,383
I've never experienced losing my appetite

126
00:07:26,008 --> 00:07:27,218
or having trouble sleeping.

127
00:07:27,301 --> 00:07:28,553
I don't know what that feels like.

128
00:07:29,887 --> 00:07:31,764
You'll know soon enough.

129
00:07:35,768 --> 00:07:38,354
When I was shooting my debut film,

130
00:07:38,437 --> 00:07:40,815
I prayed for the first time in my life.

131
00:07:40,898 --> 00:07:43,734
"I don't care about success.
Just let me finish this,

132
00:07:43,818 --> 00:07:46,070
and I'll never turn my back on you."

133
00:07:47,697 --> 00:07:49,657
I still go to church to this day.

134
00:07:50,658 --> 00:07:55,329
I knew I couldn't quit on my own,
even if I tried, and wondered,

135
00:07:55,413 --> 00:07:58,332
"How badly do I have to get hurt
to be pulled from the film?"

136
00:07:58,416 --> 00:08:01,127
"I wish the Grim Reaper
would come and get me."

137
00:08:07,425 --> 00:08:08,259
Hey.

138
00:08:10,177 --> 00:08:11,137
Just hang in there.

139
00:08:11,971 --> 00:08:12,805
Got it?

140
00:08:13,556 --> 00:08:15,933
Think of it as serving in the military
without the haircut.

141
00:08:16,017 --> 00:08:17,226
A year and a half, right?

142
00:08:18,686 --> 00:08:19,854
That time will pass somehow.

143
00:08:20,896 --> 00:08:22,189
Do you remember?

144
00:08:23,107 --> 00:08:24,775
When you were shooting that film,

145
00:08:24,859 --> 00:08:28,487
you called me in the middle of the night
and just sobbed without saying a word.

146
00:08:29,238 --> 00:08:31,282
-I did?
-You said one word.

147
00:08:32,283 --> 00:08:33,951
"Dong-man…"

148
00:08:36,912 --> 00:08:38,164
I thought you were howling.

149
00:08:51,927 --> 00:08:54,055
We need to push Hwang Dong-man
to his limits.

150
00:08:54,138 --> 00:08:57,600
He can either tremble in fear,
give up, and fall flat on his face,

151
00:08:57,683 --> 00:09:00,227
or he can stand up
and make something of himself.

152
00:09:00,311 --> 00:09:02,355
We need to push his limits either way.

153
00:09:02,938 --> 00:09:05,358
Do you want to spend your whole life
letting him piss you off?

154
00:09:06,359 --> 00:09:07,943
You can't spend
government funds like that.

155
00:09:08,027 --> 00:09:10,196
That's exactly what it's for.

156
00:09:10,279 --> 00:09:12,865
It's to help people
who keep falling short,

157
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:17,119
not to help people
who are already doing well.

158
00:09:20,331 --> 00:09:21,457
How many episodes have you written so far?

159
00:09:23,668 --> 00:09:25,211
Damn it.

160
00:09:30,424 --> 00:09:33,260
We have to send over
the first two episodes next week.

161
00:09:43,062 --> 00:09:44,105
Damn it.

162
00:09:53,406 --> 00:09:54,490
Come eat.

163
00:10:15,344 --> 00:10:17,179
BIG HYPE, NO SUBSTANCE
THE CAST WENT THROUGH HELL FOR THIS MOVIE

164
00:10:17,263 --> 00:10:18,597
THIS COMMENT HAS BEEN DELETED

165
00:10:20,349 --> 00:10:22,226
THIS COMMENT HAS BEEN DELETED

166
00:10:25,354 --> 00:10:26,856
EXPOSING CHOI FILM'S EXPLOITATION
OF SMALL, POWERLESS PRODUCTION COMPANIES

167
00:10:26,939 --> 00:10:28,482
THIS POST HAS BEEN DELETED

168
00:10:35,906 --> 00:10:38,409
I urgently need 1.7 million won
for my cat's treatment.

169
00:10:38,492 --> 00:10:40,286
Are there any decent loan sharks?

170
00:10:40,369 --> 00:10:41,996
There's no such thing
as "decent loan sharks."

171
00:10:42,079 --> 00:10:44,790
Loan sharks copy the entire contact list
on your phone.

172
00:10:44,874 --> 00:10:47,084
If you don't pay them back,
they press your acquaintances.

173
00:10:47,168 --> 00:10:48,335
You're basically asking for humiliation.

174
00:10:50,921 --> 00:10:54,592
If you don't pay the interest on time
or try to ghost me,

175
00:10:54,675 --> 00:10:58,179
I'll collect what you owe
from everyone in your phone.

176
00:10:58,262 --> 00:11:00,931
Don't forget I have your contact list.

177
00:11:01,015 --> 00:11:04,268
And don't even think about
going to the cops over illegal lending.

178
00:11:05,269 --> 00:11:06,103
Here.

179
00:11:07,313 --> 00:11:08,230
Hey.

180
00:11:08,856 --> 00:11:09,732
Excuse me.

181
00:11:10,733 --> 00:11:12,151
If I repay you in full today,

182
00:11:12,860 --> 00:11:14,236
how much would it be?

183
00:11:18,699 --> 00:11:19,658
I borrowed 1.7 million won

184
00:11:19,742 --> 00:11:21,577
and paid over five million
just in interest so far,

185
00:11:21,660 --> 00:11:23,829
so how can my balance be 11 million won?

186
00:11:25,206 --> 00:11:26,707
No, that's not what I'm saying.

187
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:33,839
Looks like this bastard

188
00:11:34,548 --> 00:11:35,674
came into some money.

189
00:11:36,300 --> 00:11:37,176
Well, shit.

190
00:11:38,260 --> 00:11:40,262
When can I sign the director's contract?

191
00:11:40,346 --> 00:11:43,557
We have to return the funds we got
for Knock knock knock

192
00:11:43,641 --> 00:11:46,018
and receive them again for Weather Maker,

193
00:11:46,101 --> 00:11:48,103
so it'll take about ten days.

194
00:11:48,187 --> 00:11:49,021
Why?

195
00:11:49,897 --> 00:11:51,232
Did something come up?

196
00:11:52,024 --> 00:11:53,484
No, ten days is…

197
00:11:55,653 --> 00:11:57,154
It's fine.

198
00:11:57,238 --> 00:11:59,114
It's not important. Don't worry about it.

199
00:11:59,198 --> 00:12:00,199
Talk to you later.

200
00:12:05,246 --> 00:12:07,248
It's 11.3 million won if you pay tonight

201
00:12:07,331 --> 00:12:08,707
and 11.6 million won if you pay tomorrow.

202
00:12:08,791 --> 00:12:11,001
It goes up 300,000 won a day,

203
00:12:11,085 --> 00:12:12,795
so send me the damn money.

204
00:12:39,572 --> 00:12:40,656
Did you borrow from a loan shark?

205
00:12:44,743 --> 00:12:45,578
Why?

206
00:12:47,955 --> 00:12:49,331
-Tell me.
-Stay out of it.

207
00:12:50,833 --> 00:12:52,668
I told you my film got greenlit.

208
00:12:53,544 --> 00:12:55,087
Don't try my patience.

209
00:12:55,170 --> 00:12:57,172
My head's about to explode as it is.

210
00:13:01,385 --> 00:13:02,303
What's your purpose?

211
00:13:04,763 --> 00:13:05,764
Say your film turns out well.

212
00:13:06,348 --> 00:13:07,182
Will it redeem you?

213
00:13:08,183 --> 00:13:09,184
Say your film turns out well.

214
00:13:09,810 --> 00:13:10,894
Will it save the country?

215
00:13:10,978 --> 00:13:12,146
I'll be less embarrassing!

216
00:13:12,229 --> 00:13:14,064
Your purpose in life
is to be less embarrassing?

217
00:13:14,148 --> 00:13:15,190
Yeah!

218
00:13:15,274 --> 00:13:17,026
I'm so embarrassed by who I am right now

219
00:13:17,109 --> 00:13:19,111
that becoming
a slightly less embarrassing person

220
00:13:19,194 --> 00:13:20,779
is my purpose in life!

221
00:13:20,863 --> 00:13:23,282
I don't know about any ultimate purpose,
and I don't have one!

222
00:13:23,365 --> 00:13:26,035
I just want to be
less embarrassing right now!

223
00:13:26,118 --> 00:13:28,287
I want to say, "I made one too! I did it!"

224
00:13:42,384 --> 00:13:44,470
Well, look who it is. Hwang Dong-man!

225
00:13:47,806 --> 00:13:51,185
I wanted to sue you,
but you deleted all your online posts.

226
00:13:51,769 --> 00:13:53,270
You really want to debut, huh?

227
00:13:55,898 --> 00:13:56,857
Hey, did you know?

228
00:13:58,150 --> 00:14:02,363
If I hadn't brought over Ma Jae-yeong,
you wouldn't be debuting.

229
00:14:02,446 --> 00:14:06,200
Who knew I'd play the biggest role
in getting Hwang Dong-man to debut?

230
00:14:06,909 --> 00:14:08,827
Life is ironic, isn't it?

231
00:14:09,495 --> 00:14:11,163
Everyone's placing bets

232
00:14:11,246 --> 00:14:14,708
on whether you can see this to the end.

233
00:14:14,792 --> 00:14:16,794
There's a huge betting pool now.

234
00:14:18,087 --> 00:14:19,922
Don't flop too fast, though.

235
00:14:20,005 --> 00:14:21,799
You should at least make it fun
for those watching.

236
00:14:21,882 --> 00:14:23,133
Drive safely.

237
00:14:23,217 --> 00:14:24,259
Thanks, I will.

238
00:14:25,511 --> 00:14:26,929
Hold out as long as possible!

239
00:14:27,012 --> 00:14:28,180
So we can have fun watching!

240
00:14:28,722 --> 00:14:30,182
Good luck, Hwang Dong-man!

241
00:14:52,079 --> 00:14:53,247
CONGRATS ON YOUR DEBUT!

242
00:15:10,931 --> 00:15:12,016
Blow it out.

243
00:15:16,437 --> 00:15:17,771
Congratulations.

244
00:15:21,817 --> 00:15:22,860
What did you wish for?

245
00:15:25,279 --> 00:15:26,113
I just

246
00:15:26,989 --> 00:15:28,157
wished for forgiveness.

247
00:15:30,617 --> 00:15:32,244
I couldn't wish for success

248
00:15:32,995 --> 00:15:34,413
because I've committed too many sins.

249
00:15:35,622 --> 00:15:37,207
So I thought I should repent first.

250
00:15:44,339 --> 00:15:45,382
I can't do this.

251
00:15:45,466 --> 00:15:47,843
I can't keep it in, so I'll just tell you.

252
00:15:48,343 --> 00:15:49,845
When Jun-hwan was shooting his debut film,

253
00:15:49,928 --> 00:15:52,389
he called me in the middle of the night
and sobbed.

254
00:15:53,015 --> 00:15:54,141
And I got excited.

255
00:15:54,767 --> 00:15:55,642
I thought,

256
00:15:57,186 --> 00:15:58,062
"It finally got scrapped."

257
00:16:01,565 --> 00:16:02,524
I want to atone.

258
00:16:02,608 --> 00:16:04,276
I want to atone so badly.

259
00:16:04,860 --> 00:16:07,071
They all worked so hard
to get to where they are

260
00:16:07,154 --> 00:16:09,031
with such desperate determination.

261
00:16:09,782 --> 00:16:11,784
I sincerely want to apologize.

262
00:16:14,203 --> 00:16:16,914
Dear God, please forgive me.

263
00:16:17,790 --> 00:16:18,665
Please…

264
00:16:19,249 --> 00:16:20,209
Please…

265
00:16:21,001 --> 00:16:23,420
I'm so sorry, Jun-hwan.

266
00:16:25,089 --> 00:16:28,509
I thought getting a film greenlit
would be all I needed.

267
00:16:29,218 --> 00:16:30,135
I must be crazy.

268
00:16:30,219 --> 00:16:31,386
Why am I not happy?

269
00:16:32,012 --> 00:16:33,889
Two voices inside me are going wild.

270
00:16:33,972 --> 00:16:35,808
"I'm debuting! I'm so excited!"

271
00:16:35,891 --> 00:16:36,975
"This is bad."

272
00:16:37,643 --> 00:16:39,103
"Run away quickly."

273
00:16:39,186 --> 00:16:40,646
"Hurry, run away!"

274
00:16:41,688 --> 00:16:43,315
I have to kill off one of them.

275
00:16:44,108 --> 00:16:45,776
But how?

276
00:16:47,820 --> 00:16:51,031
What I dreaded the most
was being asked what I had filmed.

277
00:16:51,115 --> 00:16:52,491
But yay for me!

278
00:16:52,574 --> 00:16:54,326
Now I have something to say.

279
00:16:54,409 --> 00:16:57,871
Then I wonder,
"What if I can't see this through?"

280
00:16:57,955 --> 00:16:59,748
"I've never led anything in my life,

281
00:16:59,832 --> 00:17:02,292
so how can I lead 200 people?"

282
00:17:02,376 --> 00:17:03,293
"I can't do it."

283
00:17:03,377 --> 00:17:05,671
"I need to quit
before I make a fool of myself!"

284
00:17:05,754 --> 00:17:07,214
"Shut up, I'm doing this!"

285
00:17:11,009 --> 00:17:12,761
It'll be incredibly scary.

286
00:17:14,930 --> 00:17:16,181
But I'm even more afraid…

287
00:17:19,226 --> 00:17:20,394
of looking pathetic

288
00:17:21,562 --> 00:17:22,896
if I admit I'm scared.

289
00:17:38,745 --> 00:17:39,913
Don't worry.

290
00:17:41,832 --> 00:17:45,878
If you want to run away,
I'll do whatever it takes to help you.

291
00:17:48,380 --> 00:17:50,591
Fear isn't something you endure.

292
00:17:51,466 --> 00:17:53,177
You can't endure it.

293
00:17:54,136 --> 00:17:57,014
What kind of reward
justifies putting up with that?

294
00:17:58,974 --> 00:18:00,267
I won't let you go through that.

295
00:18:06,398 --> 00:18:07,482
When I was young…

296
00:18:10,402 --> 00:18:12,779
there was only one reason

297
00:18:13,488 --> 00:18:14,573
I wanted to grow up.

298
00:18:17,409 --> 00:18:19,286
So I could leave at any time.

299
00:18:22,039 --> 00:18:24,416
So I wouldn't have to endure
going through hell.

300
00:18:26,877 --> 00:18:30,464
My heart would pound so hard
that I couldn't even tell where it was.

301
00:18:33,091 --> 00:18:35,093
But I went to school
like nothing happened,

302
00:18:36,970 --> 00:18:38,138
ate alone,

303
00:18:39,806 --> 00:18:40,807
and slept alone.

304
00:18:43,560 --> 00:18:44,519
I used to feel

305
00:18:46,104 --> 00:18:47,064
that kind of fear.

306
00:18:49,233 --> 00:18:51,360
But I won't let you go through that.

307
00:19:19,930 --> 00:19:21,848
If you want to run away together,

308
00:19:23,141 --> 00:19:25,060
I'll run away with you.

309
00:19:26,979 --> 00:19:28,981
If you want to live in hiding forever,

310
00:19:30,357 --> 00:19:31,984
I'll hide with you.

311
00:19:36,822 --> 00:19:37,739
I like that.

312
00:19:53,755 --> 00:19:55,924
I'm such a lunatic.

313
00:19:56,550 --> 00:19:58,135
Even now,

314
00:19:58,218 --> 00:20:01,013
I'm still thinking about
my acceptance speech.

315
00:20:01,930 --> 00:20:02,848
Give your speech now.

316
00:20:03,849 --> 00:20:05,017
You need to practice.

317
00:20:05,100 --> 00:20:05,934
Come on.

318
00:20:07,978 --> 00:20:08,812
Ready.

319
00:20:09,438 --> 00:20:10,564
Action.

320
00:20:11,398 --> 00:20:15,777
The 2027 Korean Film Awards
Best New Director Award goes to…

321
00:20:16,570 --> 00:20:18,196
Drumroll, please.

322
00:20:18,780 --> 00:20:22,409
Hwang Dong-man for Weather Maker!

323
00:20:40,969 --> 00:20:43,472
I imagined the moment I would stand here

324
00:20:45,057 --> 00:20:46,516
every single day.

325
00:20:47,768 --> 00:20:49,936
And I finally made it.

326
00:20:53,815 --> 00:20:55,609
I want to say this to my friends.

327
00:20:57,319 --> 00:20:58,487
Congratulate me.

328
00:21:00,072 --> 00:21:01,281
Just congratulate me.

329
00:21:02,491 --> 00:21:04,159
I'm sorry I felt sick with jealousy…

330
00:21:06,119 --> 00:21:07,621
every time your films got greenlit.

331
00:21:08,372 --> 00:21:09,998
I'm sorry I felt happy

332
00:21:10,624 --> 00:21:12,250
every time they flopped.

333
00:21:13,001 --> 00:21:14,503
But just congratulate me.

334
00:21:15,295 --> 00:21:17,547
Congratulate me from the heart.

335
00:21:20,550 --> 00:21:21,718
Congratulations!

336
00:21:22,677 --> 00:21:24,054
Congratulations!

337
00:21:27,015 --> 00:21:27,849
And…

338
00:21:30,018 --> 00:21:30,936
to Ms. Byeon Eun-a.

339
00:21:34,606 --> 00:21:35,899
If it hadn't been for you…

340
00:21:38,193 --> 00:21:41,488
I wouldn't be standing here right now.

341
00:21:44,282 --> 00:21:45,325
Thank you.

342
00:22:19,734 --> 00:22:21,361
Now that I think about it,

343
00:22:21,445 --> 00:22:23,822
it wasn't half as scary as I had imagined

344
00:22:25,657 --> 00:22:28,118
when people found out I was unemployed.

345
00:22:30,620 --> 00:22:31,580
Maybe fear

346
00:22:31,663 --> 00:22:33,832
is only in our imagination.

347
00:22:33,915 --> 00:22:36,001
When you actually face it,
it might not be so scary.

348
00:22:39,754 --> 00:22:41,256
Whenever you feel scared,

349
00:22:42,632 --> 00:22:44,885
imagine that you're the guy next door.

350
00:22:47,095 --> 00:22:49,764
If the guy next door is in your situation,

351
00:22:50,724 --> 00:22:52,100
you'll think, "It's not a big deal."

352
00:22:54,561 --> 00:22:56,271
Other people's problems
are never a big deal.

353
00:23:03,320 --> 00:23:05,530
I'd like to cautiously offer a suggestion.

354
00:23:06,198 --> 00:23:07,741
What if your younger self

355
00:23:08,825 --> 00:23:10,076
was the kid next door?

356
00:23:12,162 --> 00:23:12,996
Would it help you

357
00:23:14,080 --> 00:23:16,249
let go of your fear a bit?

358
00:23:21,254 --> 00:23:23,423
If the kid next door
was going through that…

359
00:23:27,010 --> 00:23:28,678
I'll have to take them in.

360
00:23:38,647 --> 00:23:39,773
Ms. Ga Su-ja?

361
00:23:40,815 --> 00:23:42,067
-Yes?
-Please come in.

362
00:23:42,150 --> 00:23:42,984
Okay.

363
00:23:43,777 --> 00:23:45,612
There's really no need for this.

364
00:23:45,695 --> 00:23:46,947
Come on, get up.

365
00:23:48,198 --> 00:23:49,658
My goodness.

366
00:23:54,746 --> 00:23:57,374
WE SELL GIMBAP

367
00:23:57,457 --> 00:23:59,626
She's only getting her right knee done.

368
00:23:59,709 --> 00:24:01,336
It'll be a two-week hospital stay.

369
00:24:04,381 --> 00:24:06,591
You don't have to fly in.

370
00:24:06,675 --> 00:24:08,802
It's the end of the year,
so I bet things are busy at the store.

371
00:24:10,428 --> 00:24:13,098
Don't worry, Mom.
I have more money than you.

372
00:24:15,684 --> 00:24:17,185
I'm saying I have it because I do.

373
00:24:18,645 --> 00:24:20,772
Why would I take out a loan?

374
00:24:22,315 --> 00:24:25,360
The screenplay
still doesn't have a sharp feel to it.

375
00:24:25,944 --> 00:24:29,239
It seems the director prefers
an ending that lingers

376
00:24:29,322 --> 00:24:32,409
rather than a neatly resolved one.

377
00:24:32,492 --> 00:24:35,120
There's a difference
between lingering and incomplete.

378
00:24:36,496 --> 00:24:38,623
It feels like it could go further,
but it doesn't.

379
00:24:38,707 --> 00:24:40,166
Tell them to think it over again.

380
00:24:40,250 --> 00:24:41,626
Okay, I will.

381
00:24:41,710 --> 00:24:44,212
I'm not saying
it should be patched up with dialogue.

382
00:24:44,296 --> 00:24:45,422
There's already enough of that.

383
00:24:45,505 --> 00:24:46,339
Understood.

384
00:24:48,675 --> 00:24:51,803
I heard Choi Film got a good screenplay.

385
00:24:51,886 --> 00:24:52,929
Knock knock knock, was it?

386
00:24:53,555 --> 00:24:54,431
Bring it to me.

387
00:24:55,765 --> 00:24:59,185
But Mr. Noh Kang-sik
has already been cast for the role.

388
00:24:59,269 --> 00:25:00,437
I said bring it to me.

389
00:25:02,230 --> 00:25:03,064
Okay.

390
00:25:07,610 --> 00:25:10,572
Don't pay attention to anyone
accusing you of betrayal.

391
00:25:10,655 --> 00:25:13,616
If you make a hit, they'll disappear.

392
00:25:14,242 --> 00:25:16,786
If you're a pro,
you're forgiven for anything.

393
00:25:17,370 --> 00:25:18,204
Here you go.

394
00:25:19,372 --> 00:25:20,498
Let's make a blockbuster.

395
00:25:21,082 --> 00:25:22,083
Thank you.

396
00:25:22,167 --> 00:25:23,710
You know the title has to change, right?

397
00:25:23,793 --> 00:25:27,422
The screenplay is amazing,
but what's up with Knock knock knock?

398
00:25:27,505 --> 00:25:29,883
You don't get a title by mulling it over.

399
00:25:29,966 --> 00:25:31,634
It'll come out of nowhere one day.

400
00:25:31,718 --> 00:25:34,763
It'll raise its hand and yell,
"Here I am!" so don't worry about it.

401
00:25:36,389 --> 00:25:37,849
By the way, who's Yeong-sil?

402
00:25:39,017 --> 00:25:40,310
Your girlfriend?

403
00:25:40,393 --> 00:25:42,020
She's just

404
00:25:42,645 --> 00:25:43,730
a good friend.

405
00:25:43,813 --> 00:25:47,067
It felt like one person wrote it.
The flow and tone matched perfectly.

406
00:25:47,692 --> 00:25:48,860
You two should date.

407
00:25:50,111 --> 00:25:51,279
Not quite there yet?

408
00:25:52,572 --> 00:25:54,657
How much will Yeong-sil get paid?

409
00:25:55,700 --> 00:25:57,619
Has she signed a contract
with Kopark Film?

410
00:25:58,328 --> 00:25:59,496
No, not yet.

411
00:25:59,579 --> 00:26:01,373
Tell her I want to meet her.

412
00:26:01,956 --> 00:26:04,334
Tell her I'll sign her
for the highest fee in the industry.

413
00:26:05,210 --> 00:26:07,003
She'll be shocked at the amount.

414
00:26:08,046 --> 00:26:09,589
Oh, but the thing is,

415
00:26:10,799 --> 00:26:13,176
she doesn't like revealing herself.

416
00:26:14,135 --> 00:26:14,969
Why?

417
00:26:16,471 --> 00:26:17,889
Does she like being mysterious?

418
00:26:17,972 --> 00:26:20,016
She still has to sign the contract.

419
00:26:20,100 --> 00:26:22,727
Just tell her to meet me.
I'll treat her to an expensive meal.

420
00:26:26,773 --> 00:26:27,690
Is Yeong-sil

421
00:26:29,442 --> 00:26:31,152
under contract somewhere else?

422
00:26:32,946 --> 00:26:34,197
That was lovely.

423
00:26:34,280 --> 00:26:36,116
-It was a nice meal.
-Yes, I enjoyed it too.

424
00:26:40,412 --> 00:26:42,497
Hey, Ms. Ko. Fancy meeting you here.

425
00:26:45,875 --> 00:26:46,876
Hello.

426
00:26:47,669 --> 00:26:48,962
What did you have?

427
00:26:49,045 --> 00:26:49,879
Barbecue.

428
00:26:50,755 --> 00:26:52,799
You chose an expensive place to eat,
didn't you?

429
00:26:53,466 --> 00:26:54,884
I guess the KFA funds came through.

430
00:26:54,968 --> 00:26:56,261
I'm paying for it myself.

431
00:26:59,722 --> 00:27:01,599
You're so impulsive.

432
00:27:02,976 --> 00:27:04,894
Either swallow your pride
and stick with me,

433
00:27:04,978 --> 00:27:06,688
or just call it off completely.

434
00:27:07,355 --> 00:27:09,399
Why would you take on
Hwang Dong-man instead?

435
00:27:12,193 --> 00:27:13,027
You know, right?

436
00:27:13,111 --> 00:27:17,073
Byeon Eun-a,
who's known to revive dead screenplays,

437
00:27:17,157 --> 00:27:18,741
trashed that screenplay.

438
00:27:19,534 --> 00:27:20,869
I guess you haven't heard yet.

439
00:27:21,744 --> 00:27:24,330
That same Byeon Eun-a,
who's known to revive dead screenplays,

440
00:27:24,414 --> 00:27:26,332
helped review his screenplay.

441
00:27:28,460 --> 00:27:29,919
The revision turned out well.

442
00:27:30,545 --> 00:27:32,839
It's on a whole new level
from the one he submitted for the contest.

443
00:27:34,132 --> 00:27:36,509
If he had submitted this version,
he would've won.

444
00:27:37,135 --> 00:27:38,845
I'd love to see his film
open against Ma Jae-yeong's

445
00:27:38,928 --> 00:27:40,180
and see which one wins.

446
00:27:40,763 --> 00:27:42,474
Just tell him to see it through.

447
00:27:43,475 --> 00:27:45,185
Of course, he will.

448
00:27:45,268 --> 00:27:46,102
That's mine.

449
00:27:52,775 --> 00:27:53,610
Why are you hiding?

450
00:27:54,360 --> 00:27:55,945
A producer's career
depends on who they work with.

451
00:27:56,029 --> 00:27:57,405
You do whatever comes your way.

452
00:27:58,114 --> 00:28:00,783
Don't worry about it.
Just focus on your own work.

453
00:28:01,743 --> 00:28:03,495
I'll call you later!

454
00:28:15,256 --> 00:28:16,549
Hey, Ax.

455
00:28:21,721 --> 00:28:22,889
Why don't you just…

456
00:28:25,433 --> 00:28:26,559
go to Kopark Film?

457
00:28:26,643 --> 00:28:28,603
Be the producer for Hwang Dong-man's film.

458
00:28:29,229 --> 00:28:32,690
Go and worry about
whether you'll get paid on time,

459
00:28:32,774 --> 00:28:34,609
and spend your entire career there.

460
00:28:34,692 --> 00:28:35,902
You get your paychecks from me,

461
00:28:35,985 --> 00:28:37,946
but go around giving feedback
on other screenplays.

462
00:28:38,029 --> 00:28:39,113
You're a real headache.

463
00:28:40,490 --> 00:28:43,493
Critiquing screenplays
doesn't make you a producer.

464
00:28:44,118 --> 00:28:45,370
Do you want to be a writer?

465
00:28:45,453 --> 00:28:46,788
Are you doing this
because you want to write?

466
00:28:46,871 --> 00:28:49,290
I've seen countless producers quit

467
00:28:49,374 --> 00:28:51,835
and spend years struggling to write,

468
00:28:51,918 --> 00:28:53,586
only to return in the end.

469
00:28:54,379 --> 00:28:56,089
It's easy to criticize
other people's writing.

470
00:28:56,172 --> 00:28:57,423
Try writing something yourself!

471
00:29:00,593 --> 00:29:03,680
If I hear you're helping someone
with their screenplay again,

472
00:29:04,514 --> 00:29:05,557
it won't end well.

473
00:29:07,183 --> 00:29:08,142
Oh jeez.

474
00:29:09,435 --> 00:29:10,603
Do we have indigestion meds?

475
00:29:27,620 --> 00:29:28,872
MA JAE-YEONG

476
00:29:28,955 --> 00:29:31,374
We'll be signing
a writer's contract with Choi Film,

477
00:29:31,457 --> 00:29:32,750
so find someone to front it for you.

478
00:29:52,145 --> 00:29:53,980
-Wow, she's so pretty.
-She's like a doll.

479
00:29:54,647 --> 00:29:55,899
Isn't that Jang Mi-ran?

480
00:29:55,982 --> 00:29:57,734
-It is.
-No way.

481
00:30:02,405 --> 00:30:03,823
It's been a year since we filmed it.

482
00:30:03,907 --> 00:30:05,491
How am I meant to remember
how I felt then?

483
00:30:05,575 --> 00:30:09,037
Oh, there's no pressure.
You can just say what comes to mind.

484
00:30:10,121 --> 00:30:11,706
Dramas aren't good if you sit on them.

485
00:30:11,789 --> 00:30:15,251
They feel like leftover stock
that has lost its appeal.

486
00:30:15,335 --> 00:30:17,503
I wouldn't say we sit on them.

487
00:30:17,587 --> 00:30:19,213
A lot of work
goes into post-production, so…

488
00:30:19,297 --> 00:30:21,507
You're the only ones
who'd know the details.

489
00:30:21,591 --> 00:30:23,468
The average viewer has no idea.

490
00:30:24,928 --> 00:30:27,805
I liked it better when we shot
and aired it right away.

491
00:30:31,768 --> 00:30:34,062
-Hello!
-Oh, hey.

492
00:30:34,145 --> 00:30:36,773
-How are you doing, sir?
-How long has it been?

493
00:30:37,774 --> 00:30:38,608
Hello.

494
00:30:38,691 --> 00:30:39,859
-Take a seat.
-Hello.

495
00:30:39,943 --> 00:30:40,902
Hello.

496
00:30:43,488 --> 00:30:45,782
-It's been a while, Mi-ran.
-Yeah, it has.

497
00:30:48,493 --> 00:30:49,869
So we're going to ask you

498
00:30:49,953 --> 00:30:52,664
to share some moments
you remember from the shoot

499
00:30:52,747 --> 00:30:55,124
and what you will do for the fans
if it hits the streaming charts.

500
00:30:56,167 --> 00:31:00,004
I want everyone here
to love anyone this winter.

501
00:31:01,381 --> 00:31:05,885
The director said that you two
had such strong chemistry

502
00:31:05,969 --> 00:31:07,804
that it made him wonder
if you were really in love.

503
00:31:07,887 --> 00:31:08,888
Can you elaborate on that?

504
00:31:09,806 --> 00:31:12,642
Oh, my seven-year relationship
is still going strong.

505
00:31:14,644 --> 00:31:17,981
Honestly, my character is way more lovable
than I am in real life.

506
00:31:18,064 --> 00:31:20,274
Some lines made me wonder
how one could say such things to a woman.

507
00:31:20,858 --> 00:31:23,653
Personally, I found it
a bit embarrassing at first,

508
00:31:23,736 --> 00:31:26,614
but once I got into it,
I found it oddly satisfying.

509
00:31:26,698 --> 00:31:28,741
I even got carried away later on.

510
00:31:29,701 --> 00:31:32,662
I think people appreciated me
really committing to it.

511
00:31:32,745 --> 00:31:33,746
Thank you.

512
00:31:34,372 --> 00:31:36,332
Let's move on to the next question.

513
00:31:46,259 --> 00:31:47,093
Hello?

514
00:31:47,176 --> 00:31:48,970
It looks like you betrayed me.

515
00:31:49,053 --> 00:31:51,222
I heard you dropped out
of Director Lee Jun-hwan's film.

516
00:31:52,682 --> 00:31:54,517
Let's meet up.

517
00:31:57,520 --> 00:31:59,897
Why are there so many rom-coms
in South Korea?

518
00:31:59,981 --> 00:32:02,984
I don't think love is a good emotion.

519
00:32:03,067 --> 00:32:04,944
Being in love means you're crazy.

520
00:32:05,028 --> 00:32:06,654
You're not in your right mind.

521
00:32:06,738 --> 00:32:09,282
Is there anything good
about falling in love? No.

522
00:32:09,365 --> 00:32:11,534
Do you like being in love
with Hwang Dong-man?

523
00:32:12,118 --> 00:32:13,578
That's not love. That's support.

524
00:32:13,661 --> 00:32:14,996
Supporting someone is good.

525
00:32:20,209 --> 00:32:21,836
Damn it.

526
00:32:21,919 --> 00:32:24,130
Love from viewers, my ass.

527
00:32:24,922 --> 00:32:27,175
I'd settle for them not talking trash.

528
00:32:27,258 --> 00:32:28,634
Actors seem pretty tough, right?

529
00:32:28,718 --> 00:32:30,928
We have really low self-esteem.

530
00:32:31,012 --> 00:32:33,056
We're just people waiting to be used.

531
00:32:33,639 --> 00:32:36,726
No matter how much we want to work,
we have to be chosen to do so.

532
00:32:36,809 --> 00:32:38,478
It's not something we can do on our own.

533
00:32:38,561 --> 00:32:42,482
That's why we spend time alone,
drawing and making things.

534
00:32:43,149 --> 00:32:44,442
It's the same with producers.

535
00:32:45,068 --> 00:32:46,611
We can't do anything on our own.

536
00:32:47,987 --> 00:32:50,073
Writers seem like they've got it good.

537
00:32:50,156 --> 00:32:51,407
They can start whenever,

538
00:32:51,491 --> 00:32:53,534
and everything they write
becomes their asset.

539
00:32:53,618 --> 00:32:55,953
Why don't you become a writer?
You're good at reviewing screenplays.

540
00:32:56,037 --> 00:32:59,207
Being a good reviewer
doesn't make you a good writer.

541
00:33:00,291 --> 00:33:01,459
But…

542
00:33:02,627 --> 00:33:04,337
I'm good at reviewing and writing.

543
00:33:05,880 --> 00:33:06,964
You're so annoying.

544
00:33:07,715 --> 00:33:10,676
I didn't ask to meet you
so you could annoy me.

545
00:33:11,636 --> 00:33:13,429
My mind is just

546
00:33:13,513 --> 00:33:17,350
floating around
all over the place right now.

547
00:33:19,519 --> 00:33:21,521
But I don't want to
come back down to earth.

548
00:33:24,023 --> 00:33:26,067
But I might want to at some point,

549
00:33:26,150 --> 00:33:28,402
so I'm keeping my control tower
right here.

550
00:33:28,486 --> 00:33:29,862
Can I get another beer?

551
00:33:30,530 --> 00:33:31,489
Yes, ma'am.

552
00:33:31,572 --> 00:33:33,491
Hey, isn't that Jang Mi-ran?

553
00:33:34,992 --> 00:33:36,994
I think you're right. The cringe acting.

554
00:33:40,873 --> 00:33:41,707
Hey!

555
00:33:42,625 --> 00:33:45,169
I'm way fucking past
my cringe-acting days.

556
00:33:45,253 --> 00:33:46,754
Why are you still going on about that?

557
00:33:47,755 --> 00:33:50,091
-Watch my drama that airs tomorrow!
-No, no, no.

558
00:33:51,050 --> 00:33:52,927
Let's go get some fresh air.

559
00:33:53,010 --> 00:33:54,595
-Watch it and see if my acting is cringe!
-I'm sorry.

560
00:33:54,679 --> 00:33:57,140
-It's called I'll Love Anyone This Winter!
-I'm sorry.

561
00:33:57,223 --> 00:33:58,349
It's winter, you assholes!

562
00:33:58,432 --> 00:33:59,600
Get busy falling in love

563
00:33:59,684 --> 00:34:01,394
-instead of drinking around!
-Let's get some fresh air.

564
00:34:06,357 --> 00:34:08,818
I thought the life of a star
would be different.

565
00:34:11,821 --> 00:34:16,117
Someone once asked
what life as a star was like,

566
00:34:16,993 --> 00:34:18,536
and Oh Jeong-hui said,

567
00:34:19,495 --> 00:34:22,415
"It's the same as yours,
but without the money struggles."

568
00:34:23,875 --> 00:34:25,084
I just have a bit more money.

569
00:34:26,419 --> 00:34:27,753
Everything else is the same.

570
00:34:29,005 --> 00:34:31,799
It all sucks.

571
00:34:37,054 --> 00:34:38,973
To be honest, I can't act.

572
00:34:41,350 --> 00:34:43,561
The second I say "I love you,"

573
00:34:44,937 --> 00:34:47,273
I actually start having those feelings.

574
00:34:48,441 --> 00:34:51,110
Just like how I couldn't use my arm
after that scene where I cut it off.

575
00:34:53,905 --> 00:34:55,323
When I say "I love you"…

576
00:34:57,617 --> 00:34:59,202
I actually fall in love.

577
00:35:01,287 --> 00:35:02,163
Passionately.

578
00:35:07,335 --> 00:35:08,169
But guess what?

579
00:35:11,839 --> 00:35:13,382
That jerk said he was just acting.

580
00:35:18,512 --> 00:35:21,057
How could all of that
have just been acting?

581
00:35:25,061 --> 00:35:26,520
How could

582
00:35:27,730 --> 00:35:29,023
all of that…

583
00:35:32,109 --> 00:35:33,778
have just been acting?

584
00:35:37,949 --> 00:35:39,951
I get so upset that I wake up
in the middle of the night.

585
00:35:43,955 --> 00:35:46,040
After finishing a project,

586
00:35:47,124 --> 00:35:49,168
I feel like I've been covered in filth,

587
00:35:51,003 --> 00:35:53,256
like I've been used up and thrown away.

588
00:36:10,439 --> 00:36:11,774
This isn't good.

589
00:36:19,073 --> 00:36:20,574
I'm starting to like you.

590
00:36:53,065 --> 00:36:55,067
BY MA JAE-YEONG, YEONG-SIL

591
00:37:04,785 --> 00:37:06,954
If all people were born
from a bamboo shoot…

592
00:37:07,038 --> 00:37:08,205
I wish I had been born

593
00:37:08,289 --> 00:37:09,957
-from a bamboo shoot.
-…and there's no one to blame…

594
00:37:10,958 --> 00:37:13,836
She looks like
she's fed on fear her entire life,

595
00:37:14,795 --> 00:37:15,629
like a mass of fear.

596
00:37:15,713 --> 00:37:16,839
When I look at the streets,

597
00:37:17,965 --> 00:37:19,967
I don't see people walking.

598
00:37:20,676 --> 00:37:22,970
I see masses of emotion walking around.

599
00:37:25,014 --> 00:37:26,140
That's why…

600
00:37:26,223 --> 00:37:27,058
People are all…

601
00:37:27,141 --> 00:37:28,726
I don't see them as people,

602
00:37:28,809 --> 00:37:31,062
-…masses of emotion.
-but as masses of emotion.

603
00:37:31,145 --> 00:37:33,856
PEOPLE ARE ALL… MASSES OF EMOTION

604
00:37:48,454 --> 00:37:49,914
Are my thoughts the real me?

605
00:37:50,539 --> 00:37:51,540
Or is my body the real me?

606
00:37:52,666 --> 00:37:53,667
Mom.

607
00:37:54,543 --> 00:37:56,629
Are my thoughts the real me,
or is my body the real me?

608
00:37:57,671 --> 00:38:00,132
My thoughts can go anywhere

609
00:38:00,216 --> 00:38:01,634
and do anything.

610
00:38:01,717 --> 00:38:04,345
My thoughts can do everything,
so isn't that the real me?

611
00:38:12,019 --> 00:38:12,853
Knock knock knock

612
00:38:13,938 --> 00:38:14,897
is good.

613
00:38:18,234 --> 00:38:19,068
CEO CHOI DONG-HYEON

614
00:38:19,151 --> 00:38:20,111
Isn't it amazing?

615
00:38:21,404 --> 00:38:23,280
Who's Yeong-sil?

616
00:38:23,906 --> 00:38:25,157
It sounds like a pseudonym.

617
00:38:26,742 --> 00:38:29,662
I don't know yet.
They want to remain anonymous.

618
00:39:07,533 --> 00:39:09,827
TRAITS OF A VILLAIN…
SOMETHING SCARY…

619
00:39:16,625 --> 00:39:18,294
Who's your top choice?

620
00:39:19,253 --> 00:39:20,129
Noh Kang-sik.

621
00:39:22,131 --> 00:39:23,507
I just threw it out there.

622
00:39:24,675 --> 00:39:25,593
Let's give it a shot.

623
00:39:26,552 --> 00:39:27,720
What's there to lose?

624
00:39:36,896 --> 00:39:39,023
LOAN SHARK

625
00:39:44,403 --> 00:39:45,237
Hello?

626
00:39:45,321 --> 00:39:47,114
You fucking piece of shit!

627
00:39:47,198 --> 00:39:48,199
Hey, asshole!

628
00:39:57,041 --> 00:39:58,042
You know,

629
00:39:58,542 --> 00:40:02,046
my favorite thing in the world
is hearing you type.

630
00:40:03,130 --> 00:40:05,883
Clickety-clack, clickety-clack.

631
00:40:08,552 --> 00:40:09,678
I'm sorry.

632
00:40:09,762 --> 00:40:11,263
I wrote terribly, didn't I?

633
00:40:12,014 --> 00:40:13,807
I'll do better.

634
00:40:16,519 --> 00:40:18,312
I read Dong-man's screenplay.

635
00:40:19,647 --> 00:40:21,482
Oh, I guess it's good.

636
00:40:22,316 --> 00:40:24,568
Don't worry. Ours will be much more fun.

637
00:40:24,652 --> 00:40:26,570
Then what's with the crappy writing?

638
00:40:28,364 --> 00:40:31,158
I know you'll do well, Director Park.

639
00:40:31,784 --> 00:40:33,577
I'm just going to ride on your coattails.

640
00:40:34,870 --> 00:40:37,122
I've been really into
singing in a choir lately,

641
00:40:37,206 --> 00:40:39,750
and I actually cried on my first day.

642
00:40:40,334 --> 00:40:43,170
I barely opened my mouth,
yet beautiful sounds came out.

643
00:40:43,254 --> 00:40:46,131
Then I realized,
"Oh, I can just ride on their coattails."

644
00:40:46,215 --> 00:40:47,841
"There's happiness in that too."

645
00:40:49,426 --> 00:40:51,470
So I'm going to ride on your coattails.

646
00:40:52,096 --> 00:40:56,475
No matter what anyone says, to me,
you're the best writer in the world

647
00:40:56,559 --> 00:40:59,436
as well as the funniest and smartest.

648
00:41:08,821 --> 00:41:10,197
Your coattail-riding skills

649
00:41:11,240 --> 00:41:12,074
are exceptional.

650
00:41:17,371 --> 00:41:19,248
Looks like I'm writing the script, right?

651
00:41:19,331 --> 00:41:20,958
I'm just typing whatever.

652
00:41:21,834 --> 00:41:22,960
Just keep typing.

653
00:41:23,752 --> 00:41:25,337
-"Just keep typing."
-Something will come out.

654
00:41:26,005 --> 00:41:27,590
The sound of the keyboard
wakes up my brain.

655
00:41:28,882 --> 00:41:30,801
Don't think. Let your hands type.

656
00:41:31,385 --> 00:41:32,511
It's coming out.

657
00:41:33,095 --> 00:41:34,972
It's coming out.

658
00:41:35,055 --> 00:41:37,182
-It's coming out.
-It's coming out!

659
00:41:37,266 --> 00:41:39,351
I'm writing, I'm writing.

660
00:41:39,435 --> 00:41:40,728
Hey, I'm writing something!

661
00:41:40,811 --> 00:41:42,104
I'm typing, I'm typing.

662
00:41:42,980 --> 00:41:46,358
It's hard to get started, but once you do…

663
00:41:46,442 --> 00:41:47,651
Here we go!

664
00:41:47,735 --> 00:41:51,155
Don't think. Just let your hands type.

665
00:41:51,238 --> 00:41:53,657
Just a bit more.

666
00:41:53,741 --> 00:41:56,493
Hey! I'm writing, I'm writing!

667
00:41:56,577 --> 00:42:01,582
It's hard to start the engine,
but once it starts…

668
00:42:02,750 --> 00:42:04,251
I'm out of a crisis.

669
00:42:06,128 --> 00:42:07,254
I was so relieved

670
00:42:07,921 --> 00:42:10,883
to hear Gyeong-se would have a co-writer.

671
00:42:11,925 --> 00:42:13,135
You already know

672
00:42:13,802 --> 00:42:16,305
that all the women in his movies are you.

673
00:42:17,222 --> 00:42:19,808
You were Yeong-suk
in The Lustful Bottle Opener,

674
00:42:19,892 --> 00:42:21,560
as well as Mi-rae in Decision to Stay.

675
00:42:22,394 --> 00:42:23,228
He's only ever seen

676
00:42:24,104 --> 00:42:25,064
Ko Hye-jin.

677
00:42:26,732 --> 00:42:30,694
He likes you, respects you,
loves you, and relies on you.

678
00:42:32,446 --> 00:42:34,239
Directors feed on people's lives,

679
00:42:34,948 --> 00:42:37,242
but he stuck to you like glue

680
00:42:37,326 --> 00:42:40,037
and spent his entire life
on just one woman.

681
00:42:40,788 --> 00:42:43,290
I thought it was hopeless
unless he met another woman.

682
00:42:43,916 --> 00:42:44,833
It's such a relief

683
00:42:46,126 --> 00:42:47,753
that the woman is a writer.

684
00:42:49,338 --> 00:42:50,923
He won't be out fooling around.

685
00:42:51,882 --> 00:42:53,592
I won't complain
as long as the writing is good.

686
00:42:55,427 --> 00:42:56,845
Who cares what he does?

687
00:43:08,148 --> 00:43:09,441
This is it.

688
00:43:21,537 --> 00:43:22,913
Hey!

689
00:43:22,996 --> 00:43:25,874
Why did Oh Jeong-hui read the screenplay
I'm attached to?

690
00:43:30,087 --> 00:43:31,797
Go to Choi Film today
and sign the contract.

691
00:43:33,048 --> 00:43:34,341
Sign the contract!

692
00:43:35,467 --> 00:43:37,177
Before she pulls some weird stunt.

693
00:43:37,261 --> 00:43:38,220
I'm hanging up.

694
00:43:40,013 --> 00:43:41,849
What a load of crap.

695
00:43:42,891 --> 00:43:44,309
You know, right?

696
00:43:45,561 --> 00:43:48,147
My Mother was originally My Father.

697
00:43:48,230 --> 00:43:49,314
It was offered to me.

698
00:43:49,398 --> 00:43:52,151
But she persuaded the director
to change it to a female role,

699
00:43:52,234 --> 00:43:55,404
only to have it tank
after barely reaching six million.

700
00:43:55,487 --> 00:43:58,615
If I had done it,
I guarantee it would've hit ten million.

701
00:43:58,699 --> 00:44:00,325
Man, that damn woman…

702
00:44:00,993 --> 00:44:02,619
She did the same thing when she debuted.

703
00:44:02,703 --> 00:44:04,747
You know the story, right?

704
00:44:04,830 --> 00:44:06,915
She went in to audition
for the role of the female lead's friend,

705
00:44:07,499 --> 00:44:09,126
but instead performed
the female lead's lines.

706
00:44:10,377 --> 00:44:12,713
She's got a habit of stealing from others.

707
00:44:12,796 --> 00:44:15,924
That's also how she got her husband,
you know.

708
00:44:16,008 --> 00:44:19,052
He was supposed to marry Moon Ju-ryeon,
but she broke them up.

709
00:44:20,053 --> 00:44:21,889
If she tries to
pull a stunt like that on me--

710
00:44:21,972 --> 00:44:24,057
-Let's get ready!
-Okay.

711
00:44:24,141 --> 00:44:25,309
Thank you.

712
00:44:25,392 --> 00:44:26,268
Thank you.

713
00:44:26,351 --> 00:44:27,311
Wait, your script.

714
00:44:27,394 --> 00:44:29,188
It's fine. I don't need it.

715
00:44:36,653 --> 00:44:37,488
Give it to me.

716
00:44:37,571 --> 00:44:38,447
Here.

717
00:44:40,741 --> 00:44:41,784
-Hello, sir.
-Hey.

718
00:44:44,703 --> 00:44:46,580
-Time for a beating.
-Okay.

719
00:44:48,248 --> 00:44:49,374
Assistant Director, let's do it.

720
00:44:49,458 --> 00:44:50,417
Lights out.

721
00:44:55,797 --> 00:44:56,632
Let's go.

722
00:44:56,715 --> 00:44:57,591
Quiet on set.

723
00:44:57,674 --> 00:44:58,800
Ready.

724
00:44:59,259 --> 00:45:00,093
Cue!

725
00:45:01,345 --> 00:45:02,262
You know,

726
00:45:03,305 --> 00:45:06,433
I'm pretty familiar
with the look in gamblers' eyes.

727
00:45:11,980 --> 00:45:13,732
Their minds aren't with them.

728
00:45:14,942 --> 00:45:15,984
They're somewhere else.

729
00:45:16,693 --> 00:45:18,153
They're impatient.

730
00:45:18,237 --> 00:45:19,112
You know why?

731
00:45:20,447 --> 00:45:21,740
Because they need to make it all back.

732
00:45:28,539 --> 00:45:29,498
You know what?

733
00:45:30,541 --> 00:45:32,543
That look in your eyes
hasn't come back yet.

734
00:45:33,961 --> 00:45:35,295
I guess it's time for a beating.

735
00:45:47,307 --> 00:45:48,183
Cut!

736
00:45:54,606 --> 00:45:56,149
-Are you okay?
-I'm okay, sir.

737
00:45:56,233 --> 00:45:57,818
-Sorry about that.
-It's okay.

738
00:45:58,819 --> 00:46:00,862
Okay, we'll go with this.

739
00:46:01,655 --> 00:46:03,240
"Okay, we'll go with this"?

740
00:46:05,742 --> 00:46:06,868
Director!

741
00:46:07,619 --> 00:46:08,787
Yes?

742
00:46:13,625 --> 00:46:15,002
It sounds to me that it's not okay,

743
00:46:15,085 --> 00:46:16,962
but you'll just go with it anyway.

744
00:46:18,338 --> 00:46:22,050
"This is probably the best you can do."

745
00:46:22,134 --> 00:46:24,595
"Trying again won't get us anywhere,

746
00:46:26,221 --> 00:46:27,139
so let's just stop."

747
00:46:28,682 --> 00:46:29,516
Is that it?

748
00:46:29,600 --> 00:46:31,435
No, that's not what I meant.

749
00:46:32,894 --> 00:46:33,854
Let's go again.

750
00:46:36,106 --> 00:46:37,065
Got it?

751
00:46:51,496 --> 00:46:52,372
I'm sorry.

752
00:47:16,855 --> 00:47:19,650
FRONT DOOR

753
00:47:33,121 --> 00:47:34,081
It's just makeup.

754
00:47:36,333 --> 00:47:38,168
My mind is a mess,

755
00:47:38,251 --> 00:47:39,878
but I look too normal,

756
00:47:41,129 --> 00:47:42,464
so I messed up my face

757
00:47:43,215 --> 00:47:44,049
to match my mind.

758
00:47:47,386 --> 00:47:48,637
Tell me you liked me.

759
00:47:49,805 --> 00:47:52,099
I don't care
if you hate or loathe me right now.

760
00:47:52,182 --> 00:47:53,266
Just be honest

761
00:47:54,351 --> 00:47:55,352
and say you liked me

762
00:47:56,603 --> 00:47:57,729
back then.

763
00:48:00,273 --> 00:48:03,443
How many times do I have to tell you
that I was just acting?

764
00:48:03,527 --> 00:48:04,486
Really?

765
00:48:06,363 --> 00:48:07,906
You're telling me
you're that good of an actor?

766
00:48:09,616 --> 00:48:11,159
Do you really think you're that good…

767
00:48:13,161 --> 00:48:14,121
at acting?

768
00:48:15,664 --> 00:48:17,416
I watched everything you were in.

769
00:48:17,499 --> 00:48:19,126
I even watched your debut work

770
00:48:19,209 --> 00:48:20,919
to see if you were just acting.

771
00:48:21,670 --> 00:48:24,131
I'd believe you if I had seen
that same look even once in any of them.

772
00:48:25,674 --> 00:48:27,217
But I didn't. Not once.

773
00:48:27,801 --> 00:48:29,094
It was real for you too.

774
00:48:29,177 --> 00:48:31,138
Of course, it was real.
I don't fake my acting.

775
00:48:31,221 --> 00:48:33,932
You can't help but feel emotions
when you act.

776
00:48:34,015 --> 00:48:37,769
When I do stabbing scenes,
a murderous impulse rises in me.

777
00:48:37,853 --> 00:48:39,146
Does that make me a murderer?

778
00:48:39,229 --> 00:48:41,481
You were affectionate toward me
off-camera too!

779
00:48:41,565 --> 00:48:43,525
Why did you drunk dial me?

780
00:48:43,608 --> 00:48:45,527
Why did you get in my car
on the last day of filming,

781
00:48:45,610 --> 00:48:47,446
sit there in silence, and then leave?

782
00:48:47,529 --> 00:48:49,281
Just report that crazy bitch!

783
00:48:49,364 --> 00:48:50,449
Come out here.

784
00:48:51,783 --> 00:48:53,452
Come out. I said come out!

785
00:48:53,535 --> 00:48:54,411
Hey.

786
00:48:54,494 --> 00:48:56,329
I said come out here!

787
00:48:56,413 --> 00:48:57,622
Just stop already!

788
00:49:00,667 --> 00:49:02,419
Tell him I'll talk to her

789
00:49:02,502 --> 00:49:04,212
and that it'll never happen again.

790
00:49:16,391 --> 00:49:18,226
Did you go see Jung Hyeon-u again?

791
00:49:20,479 --> 00:49:21,438
Cut it out.

792
00:49:23,815 --> 00:49:26,735
I told his people it won't happen again.

793
00:49:26,818 --> 00:49:29,696
Don't give them a reason
to report you as a stalker.

794
00:49:32,866 --> 00:49:34,785
My drama started. Are you not going to
watch this one either?

795
00:49:36,828 --> 00:49:37,996
Can't you just watch it?

796
00:49:38,663 --> 00:49:39,748
I did well this time.

797
00:49:39,831 --> 00:49:41,374
I don't even watch my own.

798
00:49:47,047 --> 00:49:49,299
I acted for real this time!

799
00:50:02,437 --> 00:50:03,396
It's acting.

800
00:50:04,481 --> 00:50:05,607
Don't do it for real.

801
00:50:06,316 --> 00:50:07,609
Just make it feel real.

802
00:50:36,221 --> 00:50:38,181
LOAN SHARK

803
00:50:44,563 --> 00:50:46,565
-Hello?
-You motherfucker.

804
00:50:46,648 --> 00:50:48,400
How dare you
not pick up my call right away?

805
00:50:48,483 --> 00:50:51,236
You fucking piece of shit.
I'll beat the shit out of you.

806
00:50:51,319 --> 00:50:54,698
If you've got money, pay me back first.
Why the hell are you ignoring me?

807
00:50:54,781 --> 00:50:57,033
You'd better send me
11.9 million won by today.

808
00:50:57,117 --> 00:50:59,744
If you don't,
I'll text everyone in your contact list

809
00:50:59,828 --> 00:51:02,372
all day and night, you motherfucker.

810
00:51:03,123 --> 00:51:04,124
Excuse me.

811
00:51:04,207 --> 00:51:07,002
I used to get really stressed out
whenever you called.

812
00:51:08,795 --> 00:51:10,714
I thought it was because I was scared,

813
00:51:12,549 --> 00:51:13,758
but it was because I was fed up.

814
00:51:13,842 --> 00:51:14,676
FED UP

815
00:51:15,260 --> 00:51:16,803
To be honest, the way you talk

816
00:51:17,470 --> 00:51:18,388
is outdated.

817
00:51:19,055 --> 00:51:20,056
It doesn't scare me at all.

818
00:51:20,140 --> 00:51:21,141
You little…

819
00:51:21,224 --> 00:51:22,767
Are you out of your mind, little fucker?

820
00:51:22,851 --> 00:51:24,436
You motherfucking piece of shit!

821
00:51:24,519 --> 00:51:26,813
Are you running your mouth
because you want to die?

822
00:51:26,897 --> 00:51:28,940
I'll slice your gut open,
rip out your organs,

823
00:51:29,024 --> 00:51:30,775
and make a fucking soup with them!

824
00:51:30,859 --> 00:51:33,528
I'll gouge your eyes out with a hook
and chew them up!

825
00:51:33,612 --> 00:51:35,071
I'll rip out all your intestines

826
00:51:35,155 --> 00:51:37,407
and lay them out
like a fucking red carpet!

827
00:51:37,490 --> 00:51:38,617
Excuse me.

828
00:51:39,451 --> 00:51:42,245
You've never ripped out organs
or gouged out eyes before, have you?

829
00:51:43,163 --> 00:51:45,248
What the fuck? You little bastard.

830
00:51:45,332 --> 00:51:48,585
They say cliché writing comes from
a lack of understanding of the world.

831
00:51:48,668 --> 00:51:52,923
When I see writing that's full of clichés,
I feel like killing someone.

832
00:51:53,006 --> 00:51:55,634
It makes me want to
smash their goddamn head with my phone.

833
00:51:55,717 --> 00:51:57,552
These so-called writers

834
00:51:57,636 --> 00:52:00,347
keep pumping out familiar crap,
and you're no different, you asshole.

835
00:52:00,430 --> 00:52:02,057
You scare people for a living,

836
00:52:02,140 --> 00:52:04,142
but you never stop to think about
what actually scares them.

837
00:52:04,225 --> 00:52:06,102
It's always the same thing
about ripping out organs

838
00:52:06,186 --> 00:52:07,270
and gouging out eyeballs.

839
00:52:07,354 --> 00:52:08,647
-Is that all you can do?
-You fucking asshole.

840
00:52:08,730 --> 00:52:10,357
-It's because of lazy bastards like you
-Shut up.

841
00:52:10,440 --> 00:52:12,484
that gangster movies in this country
are going downhill!

842
00:52:12,567 --> 00:52:14,778
-I said shut the fuck up!
-If you're going to leech off people,

843
00:52:14,861 --> 00:52:16,196
at least put in some effort!

844
00:52:16,780 --> 00:52:18,698
-Shut the hell up!
-And stop with the cliché bullshit!

845
00:52:18,782 --> 00:52:21,368
-Shut up! Shut up!
-Do you even know what "cliché" means?

846
00:52:21,451 --> 00:52:23,620
-Shut the hell up!
-Dig through that brain of yours, idiot!

847
00:52:23,703 --> 00:52:26,289
-Shut the hell up!
-It means you're lazy as hell!

848
00:52:26,373 --> 00:52:28,208
I actually want to feel scared!

849
00:52:28,291 --> 00:52:31,252
-To the point of pissing myself, asshole!
-You're dead.

850
00:52:31,878 --> 00:52:33,213
Stay right there.

851
00:52:33,296 --> 00:52:34,965
You'd better not be wearing a gold chain.

852
00:52:43,348 --> 00:52:44,349
Fucking hell.

853
00:52:46,101 --> 00:52:47,185
Goddamn it!

854
00:53:21,594 --> 00:53:22,512
Thank you.

855
00:53:41,698 --> 00:53:44,075
Come out, you fucking asshole.

856
00:53:47,287 --> 00:53:48,663
I said come out!

857
00:53:51,416 --> 00:53:52,876
Goddamn it!

858
00:53:52,959 --> 00:53:53,835
Calm down.

859
00:54:07,390 --> 00:54:08,433
Hey.

860
00:54:10,852 --> 00:54:12,771
Where's Hwang Dong-man, that motherfucker?

861
00:54:14,981 --> 00:54:16,566
Where is he?

862
00:54:17,525 --> 00:54:19,319
You fucking assholes, I'm ought to just--

863
00:54:25,658 --> 00:54:26,701
-You're bleeding.
-Shit.

864
00:54:26,785 --> 00:54:27,702
You're bleeding.

865
00:55:20,964 --> 00:55:25,218
I texted everyone in your contact list,
you fucking piece of shit.

866
00:55:25,301 --> 00:55:26,719
Go ahead and keep ignoring me.

867
00:55:26,803 --> 00:55:29,514
I'll keep harassing them
until you pay me back.

868
00:55:42,694 --> 00:55:44,529
This motherfucker, Hwang Dong-man,

869
00:55:44,612 --> 00:55:47,740
took 11.9 million won from me
and is now ghosting me.

870
00:55:47,824 --> 00:55:50,702
Brace yourselves because I'm going to
harass you day and night

871
00:55:50,785 --> 00:55:52,203
until I get my money back.

872
00:55:52,287 --> 00:55:53,204
What the heck?

873
00:55:54,414 --> 00:55:56,249
CALL THIS NUMBER IF YOU SEE HWANG DONG-MAN

874
00:55:57,500 --> 00:55:59,210
Goodness gracious.

875
00:56:00,044 --> 00:56:02,255
This is more entertaining
than most screenplays.

876
00:56:02,338 --> 00:56:04,424
He'll never complete a film at this rate.

877
00:56:06,259 --> 00:56:08,219
Good luck, Dong-man!

878
00:56:17,812 --> 00:56:19,439
He borrowed from a loan shark?

879
00:56:20,064 --> 00:56:21,858
Hwang Dong-man is really something.

880
00:56:26,529 --> 00:56:28,406
I had opened my front door for a bit

881
00:56:28,489 --> 00:56:29,991
when my cat slipped out.

882
00:56:32,076 --> 00:56:33,119
It got hit by a car

883
00:56:34,329 --> 00:56:36,331
and needed emergency surgery,

884
00:56:36,956 --> 00:56:39,959
but I had already maxed out
my credit card.

885
00:56:41,419 --> 00:56:42,378
I'm sorry.

886
00:56:48,426 --> 00:56:50,595
This is why I like you.

887
00:56:51,471 --> 00:56:53,806
A man who borrows from a loan shark
to save his cat.

888
00:56:56,059 --> 00:56:57,560
Don't worry about it.

889
00:56:57,644 --> 00:56:59,312
It'll take more than that to break you.

890
00:57:03,441 --> 00:57:06,194
Why are you always so good to me?

891
00:57:09,197 --> 00:57:10,531
Because you deserve it.

892
00:57:28,633 --> 00:57:30,260
5-MINUTE LOAN APPROVAL
NO COLLATERAL OR GUARANTOR REQUIRED

893
00:57:30,343 --> 00:57:31,261
LOANS

894
00:57:46,234 --> 00:57:48,027
The second you say something cliché,
it's over.

895
00:57:48,111 --> 00:57:49,737
"Eyeballs." "Guts."

896
00:57:50,572 --> 00:57:52,615
The second you start throwing around
words like that, it's over.

897
00:57:53,741 --> 00:57:55,451
You made a big mistake.

898
00:57:55,535 --> 00:57:57,537
Now that you've blasted my contacts,

899
00:57:57,620 --> 00:57:59,706
what's supposed to scare me
into paying you back?

900
00:58:00,748 --> 00:58:02,417
You should've been more careful.

901
00:58:03,835 --> 00:58:06,629
Did you know the chief investigator
at Mapo Police Station is in my contacts?

902
00:58:07,547 --> 00:58:08,840
He's my cousin.

903
00:58:08,923 --> 00:58:10,174
He said to bring you in.

904
00:58:12,885 --> 00:58:13,845
But right now,

905
00:58:14,679 --> 00:58:15,680
I need

906
00:58:16,514 --> 00:58:18,057
something scary.

907
00:58:18,725 --> 00:58:20,727
If you show me something really scary,

908
00:58:20,810 --> 00:58:21,644
you'll get ten million won.

909
00:58:22,895 --> 00:58:23,855
It's worth it for me.

910
00:58:23,938 --> 00:58:25,565
Out of everything you've experienced

911
00:58:26,399 --> 00:58:28,192
and everything you've done,

912
00:58:28,985 --> 00:58:30,445
I want you to tell me

913
00:58:31,821 --> 00:58:32,947
what the scariest thing was.

914
00:58:36,743 --> 00:58:37,577
Or…

915
00:58:39,078 --> 00:58:40,913
you can just scare me right now.

916
00:58:45,043 --> 00:58:45,877
Fuck!

917
00:58:48,713 --> 00:58:50,548
You people are scarier than we are.

918
00:58:51,883 --> 00:58:55,386
When we go to collect, you cut gas lines,
start fires, and swing kitchen knives.

919
00:58:55,845 --> 00:58:59,349
That's why we barge in with our shoes on.
So we can run away if we have to!

920
00:58:59,432 --> 00:59:01,851
We don't wear them inside to scare you!

921
00:59:03,728 --> 00:59:04,562
You really have nothing?

922
00:59:06,522 --> 00:59:08,024
It's your chance to make ten million won.

923
00:59:08,107 --> 00:59:09,150
Screw you.

924
00:59:13,071 --> 00:59:13,905
We're done, then.

925
00:59:13,988 --> 00:59:16,824
I borrowed 1.7 million won
and paid back 5 million won.

926
00:59:16,908 --> 00:59:17,742
That's triple the amount.

927
00:59:19,077 --> 00:59:20,703
If you keep calling or texting,

928
00:59:21,996 --> 00:59:25,124
I'm going to come at you
with everything I've got

929
00:59:25,208 --> 00:59:26,584
and end you.

930
00:59:27,919 --> 00:59:29,962
You were able to push around
the old Hwang Dong-man,

931
00:59:30,797 --> 00:59:32,215
but I'm not the same man anymore.

932
00:59:36,886 --> 00:59:38,596
As of today, we're done.

933
00:59:39,347 --> 00:59:40,223
Got it?

934
00:59:43,017 --> 00:59:44,102
We're done.

935
00:59:45,395 --> 00:59:46,229
Got it?

936
00:59:59,117 --> 01:00:00,243
How did you handle it?

937
01:00:00,910 --> 01:00:02,370
You sure you don't need money?

938
01:00:02,453 --> 01:00:03,496
Yeah, I'm good.

939
01:00:05,581 --> 01:00:09,794
By the way, do you want the villain
to be more evil or just stronger?

940
01:00:09,877 --> 01:00:10,712
What?

941
01:00:10,795 --> 01:00:13,005
Most people confuse evil with strength.

942
01:00:13,881 --> 01:00:15,717
Do I make him more evil
or make him stronger?

943
01:00:18,594 --> 01:00:19,429
Stronger.

944
01:00:20,346 --> 01:00:21,305
Okay, got it.

945
01:00:30,732 --> 01:00:32,024
There's no evil in me.

946
01:00:33,192 --> 01:00:34,026
But there is strength.

947
01:00:52,879 --> 01:00:54,672
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

948
01:01:13,483 --> 01:01:15,568
I heard you gave Noh Kang-sik
Hwang Dong-man's screenplay.

949
01:01:15,651 --> 01:01:16,944
Did you do that
because you think you've got a shot?

950
01:01:17,028 --> 01:01:18,154
Why do you keep pestering me?

951
01:01:18,988 --> 01:01:20,406
Hello!

952
01:01:20,490 --> 01:01:21,449
When will you ever shine

953
01:01:21,532 --> 01:01:23,034
if you hide behind a pseudonym?

954
01:01:24,619 --> 01:01:26,454
Did you learn how to laugh yesterday?

955
01:01:26,537 --> 01:01:28,456
We got the CCTV footage,

956
01:01:28,539 --> 01:01:29,791
so we'll be seeing you soon.

957
01:01:29,874 --> 01:01:31,125
Why did you write the protagonist as male?

958
01:01:31,209 --> 01:01:33,961
The screenplay would work just fine
with a female protagonist.

959
01:01:34,045 --> 01:01:36,964
This is the second time
he offered a role and took it back.

960
01:01:37,048 --> 01:01:39,133
-He beat up another one. Cha Jeong-min.
-It's okay. Sit down.

961
01:01:39,217 --> 01:01:41,803
Why not just work with me

962
01:01:41,886 --> 01:01:43,679
before you get canceled
for beating a junior?

963
01:01:44,722 --> 01:01:49,727
Subtitle translation by: Jenny Kim
